Me, hugging keyleth: he needs to die

summary:
Critical Role • Pikelan • Perc'ahlia Wedding
It happens like this: Vex says it's not right to make Scanlan stay at a hotel....
body:
Accidentally in Love

Critical Role • Pikelan • Perc'ahlia Wedding

It happens like this: Vex says it’s not right to make Scanlan stay at a hotel. Percy agrees; it isn’t right that he should sleep in a hotel. Not when they have a perfectly good kennel going unused. He smiles, pleasantly, at Vex, who shoots him a look that would have melted the skin off the bones of a lesser man.

So Pike says, “He can stay with me.” (Read here!)

summary: This year I challenged myself to finish some kind of creative project every month, and September's was this Critical Role...
caption:
This year I challenged myself to finish some kind of creative project every month, and September’s was this Critical Role hoodie!

The yarn was King Cole Luxury Merino Knitting Yarn DK in Midnight Blue (eight balls was just enough) and white; it stretched a lot when I blocked it, fyi.

I based the pattern on this free hoodie pattern, but a couple of rows after transferring the stitches for the sleeves to stitch holders, I divided the whole thing at the underarms and worked the front and back flat, casting on one stitch at the beginning and end of the first two rows to make sewing the seams easier later.*

I made the chart using graph paper generated on Stitch Fiddle - actually, I made three versions of the chart. First I made one of the logo alone with no letters, to make life easy for myself. But then I decided it was TOO easy and made one with the CR as in the podcast logo. As it turns out, however, I don’t quite like the size and placement of the letters in that version, so I made a THIRD version with slightly adjusted letters, which was the one I eventually ended up using.

*I have here elided a long period of knitting and unravelling and complaining and so on

excerpt: An Archive of Our Own, a project of the Organization for Transformative Works
description:
(The Last of Us AU for Critical Role, featuring Nott and Caleb)

Ever since Nott was old enough to understand anything, she’d understood about the infection. And the cities. And the military. And sometime later, she understood about the Fireflies. She avoided more or less all of it on principle. Things were like that when you’d left a group too late to join another one.

She rarely went into the city these days. There were certain tunnels the military hadn’t found yet; she used them to get in, get supplies, and get out. She always stayed on the fringes, in the shadows where she was safe from the military. She did have to contend with Infected from time to time, but they were far easier to deal with than people with guns.

But the past few days she’d been driven further into the city looking for food. Even though it was summer, the military was keeping a tight hold on their rations. Supplies must have been getting low, and people were getting desperate. People like Nott. But the food wasn’t what got her. No, what got her into trouble was a ring.
